title: Federal Statistical Directory
additional-note: This was a US government publication through the 1970s. Private companies published later editions and claimed copyright on them.  The factual information in those later directories, such as names, addresses, and telephone numbers, is not copyrightable, per the Supreme Court's 1991 ruling in Feist v. Rural Telephone Service Company.
acknowledgement: Thanks to Scott Andrews for copyright research on this title.
